                            <comment id="13925026" author="revbooyah" created="Sat, 8 Mar 2014 22:06:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I made a youtube tutorial showing a simple static mahout recommender from start to finish.  You&apos;re welcome to use any or all of it.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yD40rVKUwPI&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yD40rVKUwPI&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
-steve&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13925035" author="smarthi" created="Sat, 8 Mar 2014 22:32:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is great Steve, added a link to your youtube video at &lt;a href=&quot;http://mahout.apache.org/general/books-tutorials-and-talks.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mahout.apache.org/general/books-tutorials-and-talks.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13925149" author="ssc" created="Sun, 9 Mar 2014 08:44:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Great tutorial, I put it onto a new quickstart page for the recommenders:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mahout.apache.org/users/recommender/quickstart.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://mahout.apache.org/users/recommender/quickstart.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Btw, one question: is there a specific reason, why you did not use the maven dependency of Mahout? That way you could avoid having to manually download dependent jars&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13925162" author="ssc" created="Sun, 9 Mar 2014 09:51:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;reopening this, because it was opened by Maciej not Steve, so I guess Maciej also plans to contribute something here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13925201" author="maciejmazur" created="Sun, 9 Mar 2014 13:51:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s true. I&apos;ve another version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;May I ask whether preprocessing is really needed with this particular dataset(youtube tutorial)? I found somewhere that it works without it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have attached file here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12633591/Quickstart%20recommendation&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12633591/Quickstart%20recommendation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
It&apos;s plain text, should I format it somehow?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13925207" author="ssc" created="Sun, 9 Mar 2014 14:25:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The tutorial looks very nice. It would be great if you could add markdown formatting (our website uses this internally). You can use an online markdown editor for working on it: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ctrlshift.net/project/markdowneditor/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.ctrlshift.net/project/markdowneditor/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13925214" author="maciejmazur" created="Sun, 9 Mar 2014 15:04:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, now it looks better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13925230" author="ssc" created="Sun, 9 Mar 2014 16:20:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you. The article is now online at &lt;a href=&quot;https://mahout.apache.org/users/recommender/userbased-5-minutes.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://mahout.apache.org/users/recommender/userbased-5-minutes.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It took the freedom to shorten and rewrite it a bit. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
